# Session 4: Pipeline Backend + Frontend Editor

Read AI_CONTEXT.md for full context. Session 3 (Frontend Connections Page) is complete.

## Tasks

### Backend (Tasks 1-5)

1. **Base Node Architecture** (`backend/app/nodes/`)
   - Create `base.py` — abstract base class for all nodes
   - Create `registry.py` — node type registry
   - Create `text_output.py` — simple text output node (Hello World example)

2. **Pipeline Execution** (`backend/app/orchestration/`)
   - Create `executor.py` — orchestrates node execution via Celery
   - Create `graph_resolver.py` — topological sort, cycle detection
   - Create `context_builder.py` — resolves `{{ node_id.output }}` templates

3. **Pipeline CRUD API** (`backend/app/api/pipelines.py`)
   - POST `/api/v1/pipelines` — create pipeline
   - GET `/api/v1/pipelines` — list pipelines
   - GET `/api/v1/pipelines/{id}` — get pipeline details
   - PUT `/api/v1/pipelines/{id}` — update pipeline
   - DELETE `/api/v1/pipelines/{id}` — delete pipeline
   - POST `/api/v1/pipelines/{id}/run` — start pipeline execution

4. **Pipeline Run Logs** (`backend/app/api/pipeline_runs.py`)
   - GET `/api/v1/pipeline-runs/{id}` — get run status
   - GET `/api/v1/pipeline-runs/{id}/logs` — get logs (REST)
   - GET `/api/v1/pipeline-runs/{id}/logs/stream` — **SSE stream** (real-time)

5. **Integration Tests** (`backend/tests/integration/test_pipelines.py`)
   - Test pipeline creation
   - Test pipeline execution (text output node)
   - Test template resolution `{{ node_id.output }}`
   - Test log streaming

**⚠️ After completing backend tasks: run `pytest` and `ruff format backend/`, then proceed to frontend**

### Frontend (Tasks 6-8)

6. **TypeScript Types & API Client** (`frontend/src/`)
   - Create `types/pipeline.ts` — Pipeline, Node, Edge types
   - Create `api/pipelines.ts` — CRUD + run + logs API client
   - Create `api/pipelineRuns.ts` — SSE log streaming client

7. **Pipeline List Page** (`frontend/src/components/PipelinesPage.tsx`)
   - List all pipelines
   - Create new pipeline (name, description)
   - Delete pipeline
   - Navigate to editor

8. **Pipeline Editor Page** (`frontend/src/components/PipelineEditor.tsx`)
   - Use @xyflow/react for node-based editor
   - Add nodes from sidebar (drag-and-drop or click-to-add)
   - Connect nodes with edges
   - Configure node parameters (form modal)
   - Reference outputs from other nodes: `{{ node_id.output }}`
   - Save pipeline
   - Run pipeline and view real-time logs (SSE)

## Requirements

**Backend:**
- Celery Integration — each node runs as isolated Celery task
- Template Syntax — `{{ node_id.output_name }}` for referencing outputs
- SSE for Logs — use `aiohttp-sse` or implement manually with `StreamingResponse`
- Graph Validation — detect cycles, validate all connections exist

**Frontend:**
- @xyflow/react 12 for node editor
- Mantine components for UI
- Toast notifications for save/run results
- Real-time log viewer with auto-scroll

**Tests:**
- Integration tests with testcontainers
- Run `pytest` after backend implementation

## Rules

Follow all Development Rules in AI_CONTEXT.md:
- Run `pytest` after backend implementation
- Run `ruff format backend/` after writing code
- Verify frontend changes with user before committing
- Clean `__pycache__` before session end
- Make git commit at session end
- Do NOT start Session 5

Start with Task 1 (Base Node Architecture).